# Code owners for the kernel of the self-building organism.
#
# Every entry here mirrors one in .github/protected-paths, which is the single
# definition. This file is the projection of that list onto GitHub's review
# mechanism; scripts/check-protected-paths.sh fails when the two drift apart, so
# a path can never be protected in one place and unowned in the other.
#
# What this file does on its own: requests review from the owner when a pull
# request touches a listed path.
#
# What it does NOT do on its own: block anything. Blocking requires branch
# protection with "Require review from Code Owners" enabled on the default
# branch. See GUARDRAILS.md for which layers are enforced and which are
# advisory — this file is deliberately explicit about the difference rather
# than implying a gate that is not configured.

/.github/protected-paths            @opentendril
/.github/workflows/                 @opentendril
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @opentendril
/.github/dependabot.yml             @opentendril
/cmd/stem/main.go                   @opentendril
/cmd/stem/cmdserve.go               @opentendril
/cmd/stem/internal/core/            @opentendril
/cmd/stem/internal/conductor/protectedpaths.go  @opentendril
/scripts/                           @opentendril
/AGENTS.md                          @opentendril
/GUARDRAILS.md                      @opentendril
/ARCHITECTURE.md                    @opentendril
/SYNTHETIC-TAXONOMY.md              @opentendril
/CAPABILITIES.md                    @opentendril
/USE-CASES.md                       @opentendril
/.env                               @opentendril
